<br>
MKDA is such a fundamentally good game.  One of the only fighting games that isn't twitch.  The combinations are intuitive, and moves are not so fast that you can't see something coming at you and react accordingly.  <br>
<br>
We have a PS2, Gamecube, and Xbox in our apartment, and have played a lot of other fighting games.  These other games are littered with what we call fundamental game flaws.  These are not RPGs, these are fighting games.  Any time spent not fighting, is wasted time.  If I have to watch both characters say their line, or perform a move before each battle, I turn the game off and never play it again.  It's just a game flaw.  Mortal Kombat appears to also have the fewest game flaws of any fighting game since SNES.<br>
<br>
